title.narrative: JISRA MM Indonesia

description.narrative: The Joint Initiative for Strategic Religious Action (JISRA) is a partnership between faith and non-faith based groups – including Christian, Islamic, interreligious and secular consortium partners and local partners – which will promote Freedom of Religion or Belief (FoRB) in Ethiopia, Indonesia, Iraq, Kenya, Mali, Nigeria and Uganda. The JISRA consortium consists of Mensen met een Missie, Search for Common Ground, Faith to Action Netowrk, and Tearfund (UK and NL). JISRA is funded by the Dutch Ministry of Foreign Affairs from 2021-2025
